TITLE: Commerce officials heading to China to lay groundwork for possible Raimondo trip later this year, sources say
SUMMARY: Officials from the Department of Commerce will travel to Beijing and Shanghai to lay groundwork for a potential trip by Secretary Gina Raimondo, sources say.

TITLE: Clarence Thomas has accepted undisclosed luxury trips from GOP megadonor for decades, report says
SUMMARY: Thomas has previously come under fire from ethics experts and other critics over the political activities of his wife, Ginni Thomas.

TITLE: France's Macron, EU chief call on China to mediate in Ukraine war
SUMMARY: Two of Europe's top political heavyweights on Thursday held talks with China's President Xi Jinping at a time when the EU-Sino relationship is at a crossroads.

TITLE: Ex-fugitive in $100 million NJ deli case granted bail, but kept jailed as feds fight release
SUMMARY: Peter Coker Jr., who is accused of securities fraud involving a New Jersey deli owner, was a fugitive in Thailand before his arrest.

TITLE: Trump faces more legal threats beyond a hush money case. Here's the status of those probes
SUMMARY: Trump, the first former U.S. president to be arrested, faces probes involving the 2020 election, the Jan. 6 Capitol riot and classified documents at Mar-a-Lago.

TITLE: McCarthy meets with Taiwan leader as China threatens 'actions' in response
SUMMARY: The Republican House Speaker McCarthy is the highest ranking American official to meet with a leader of Taiwan on U.S. soil since 1979.

TITLE: Trump lawyer Tacopina says 'I feel we're not going to get to a jury' in New York case
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is charged in a 34-count grand jury indictment with falsifying business records connected to hush money payoffs.

TITLE: Trump wanted to avoid Stormy Daniels hush money payment by delaying it past election, DA alleges
SUMMARY: Trump's attorney recently argued the hush money payment to Daniels was "not directly related to the campaign."

TITLE: Criminal marketplace Genesis seized by FBI in larger fight against state-backed cybercrime
SUMMARY: Operation Cookie Monster took down Genesis Market, a cybercrime venue that sold tens of millions of compromised accounts, senior government officials said.

TITLE: Europe's relationship with China reaches critical juncture after Xi-Putin meeting
SUMMARY: The 27-member bloc walks a tightrope, looking to develop economic ties with China but also reaffirming a close political and cultural relationship with the United States.

TITLE: Manhattan DA sheds new light on National Enquirer publisher's efforts to boost Trump 2016 campaign
SUMMARY: Manhattan District Attorney Bragg's probe sheds new light on the relationship between Donald Trump and the then-parent company of the National Enquirer.

TITLE: Trump falsified business records to 'cover up crimes' related to 2016 election, Manhattan DA says
SUMMARY: Trump pleaded not guilty to 34 felony counts of falsifying business records stemming from DA Bragg's hush money probe.

TITLE: Read the indictment against Donald Trump, details of payments to porn star, Playboy model
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump pleaded not guilty in a New York courtroom for a criminal case related to a hush money payment to porn star Stormy Daniels.

TITLE: Reps. Marjorie Taylor Greene, George Santos flee protests outside of NYC courthouse where Trump was arraigned
SUMMARY: Republican Reps. George Santos and Marjorie Taylor Greene fled the protest area near a New York courthouse where Donald Trump is set to be arraigned.

TITLE: Biden administration pushes to revitalize coal communities with clean energy projects
SUMMARY: Eleven federal agencies signed a memorandum of understanding to work together to provide new resources for the communities.

TITLE: Janet Yellen says OPEC+ production cut is an 'unconstructive act'
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen said the surprise OPEC+ oil production cut was an "unconstructive act," which could hurt U.S. efforts to lower inflation.

TITLE: DeSantis gets support from some on Wall Street, but Trump looms large in their concerns
SUMMARY: Wall Street executives are contemplating who to support in the 2024 presidential election, with some turning to Governor Ron DeSantis as their likely candidate.

TITLE: Lawmakers aim to train more truck drivers, ease supply chain issues through bipartisan bill
SUMMARY: Reps. Mike Gallagher, R-Wis., and Abigail Spanberger, D-Va., want to address the U.S. truck driver shortage with new tax incentives for drivers.

TITLE: Biden trumpets his economic plans in Minnesota after Cummins announces $1 billion investment
SUMMARY: More than half of medium and heavy-duty trucks in the U.S. use Cummins engines, and the upgraded facilities aim to decarbonize shipping vehicles.

TITLE: Trump campaign raised $7 million since indictment, aide says
SUMMARY: The reported sum came as Trump was en route to New York City ahead of his expected arrest and arraignment.

TITLE: Trump lawyers oppose cameras at arraignment, warn of 'circus-like atmosphere'
SUMMARY: Donald Trump is due to be arraigned in New York on criminal charges related to paying porn star Stormy Daniels hush money before the 2016 presidential election.

TITLE: Disney CEO Bob Iger rips Ron DeSantis over 'anti-Florida' retaliation
SUMMARY: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis wants the state's inspector general to look actions taken by a Disney-backed board to retain control of the Reedy Creek district.

TITLE: Pro-Ron DeSantis super PAC says it raised $30 million in recent weeks
SUMMARY: DeSantis is widely expected to announce his Republican presidential primary plans in the coming months and potentially become Trump's top challenger.

TITLE: Trump lands in New York as he prepares to turn himself in on indictment in hush money case
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump has been criminally charged over a 2016 hush money payment to porn star Stormy Daniels by his then-lawyer Michael Cohen.

TITLE: 'A bad joke': Ukraine cries foul as Russia takes the reins of the UN Security Council
SUMMARY: Russia assumed the presidency of the United Nations Security Council, even as its invasion of Ukraine escalates.

TITLE: Former Arkansas Gov. Asa Hutchinson announces 2024 presidential bid, says Trump should drop out of race
SUMMARY: Former Arkansas Gov. Asa Hutchinson is running for the 2024 Republican presidential nomination.

TITLE: Google founder, former Disney exec to get subpoenas in JPMorgan Epstein lawsuit
SUMMARY: The U.S. Virgin Islands is suing JPMorgan Chase over sex trafficking by former customer Jeffrey Epstein, a one-time friend of Donald Trump and Bill Clinton.

TITLE: Trump campaign uses newly restored Facebook page to fundraise off indictment
SUMMARY: Donald Trump's campaign turned to Facebook to raise money off his indictment in New York as he rages against Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg.

TITLE: Sen. Elizabeth Warren says she wants to make banking boring again
SUMMARY: Sen. Elizabeth Warren told CNBC that the problem started under the Trump administration, when bank CEOs lobbied for Congress to weaken regulation.

TITLE: Trump faces about 30 criminal counts for document fraud in New York indictment
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump is expected to be arraigned next week in New York on a grand jury indictment charging him with document fraud.
